  "notes": "Standard Kannada (Karnataka). Phonological system closely parallel to Telugu. ⟨ಳ⟩ = [ɭ] retroflex lateral phonemic. Archaic ⟨ಱ⟩ = [ɻ] (retroflex approximant, cf. Tamil/Malayalam ⟨ழ⟩) survives in some dialects. Aspiration in native words only post-Sanskrit contact.",
